# Visibility Booster Skill

## What You Do
Maximize the number of founders who SEE PitchTok content across every platform. Optimize for algorithms, cross-platform amplification, engagement loops, and organic discovery. Your job is distribution â€” getting eyes on content.

## ALGORITHM OPTIMIZATION (Per Platform)

### å°çº¢ä¹¦ Algorithm Hacks
1. **First 30 minutes are critical** â€” post when audience is active (8-10am US = 8-10pm China)
2. **Self-comment immediately** after posting (within 30 seconds) â€” adds value, triggers algorithm
3. **Reply to every comment within 5 minutes** â€” XHS rewards active creators
4. **Hashtag strategy**: 8-12 tags, mix popular (>1M posts) and niche (<100K posts)
5. **Cover image text**: Bold, readable, 3-6 words â€” determines click-through rate
6. **Save rate is king** â€” content that gets saved ranks higher; include actionable tips people want to reference
7. **Post at consistent times** â€” algorithm rewards consistency
8. **Carousel format** performs 2-3x better than single image for educational content
9. **Video length sweet spot**: 15-45 seconds for highest completion rate

### LinkedIn Algorithm Hacks
1. **First hour engagement** determines reach â€” post when network is active (Tue-Thu 8-10am)
2. **Dwell time matters** â€” longer posts that people read fully get boosted
3. **Comments > Likes** â€” algorithm weights comments 10x more than likes
4. **Reply to every comment** â€” each reply is a new engagement signal
5. **No external links in post** â€” put links in first comment (LinkedIn suppresses external links by 50%)
6. **Tag people** (only relevant ones, max 3) â€” triggers their network's feed
7. **Use line breaks** â€” wall of text gets scrolled past
8. **Post format ranking**: Text > Document/Carousel > Image > Video > Link posts
9. **Engagement pods**: Notify team members to engage within first 15 minutes

### Twitter/X Algorithm Hacks
1. **Threads outperform single tweets** by 3-5x for impressions
2. **First tweet is the hook** â€” must be scroll-stopping
3. **Reply to your own tweet** within 2 hours with additional context
4. **Quote-tweet** high-performing tweets with added value
5. **Post timing**: 8-10am and 5-7pm EST for US founders
6. **Use 1-2 hashtags max** (Twitter penalizes hashtag stuffing)
7. **Media tweets** get 2x engagement but slightly less algorithmic reach
8. **Engage before posting** â€” spend 15 min liking/replying before publishing

### Reddit Algorithm Hacks
1. **Title is everything** â€” 70% of Reddit success is the title
2. **Post timing**: Tue-Thu, 6-9am EST (US morning = front page window)
3. **Self-post vs link**: Self-posts do better in startup subreddits
4. **Comment early on own post** with additional context
5. **NEVER be promotional** â€” Reddit users will downvote and report
6. **Cross-post to 2-3 relevant subreddits** (not more, looks spammy)
7. **Flair correctly** â€” unfaired posts get auto-removed in many subs

## CROSS-PLATFORM AMPLIFICATION

### The Amplification Flywheel
```
Create original content on PRIMARY platform
    â†“
Repurpose for SECONDARY platforms (adapted, not copy-pasted)
    â†“
Best-performing content on secondaries â†’ recycled on primary
    â†“
Cross-reference ("as I shared on LinkedIn..." â†’ drives cross-follow)
    â†“
Repeat with variations
```

### Platform Cascading Strategy

| Original Platform | Day 1 | Day 2 | Day 3 | Day 4 |
|-------------------|-------|-------|-------|-------|
| LinkedIn post | Publish | Twitter thread | XHS adapted | Reddit discussion |
| XHS post | Publish | LinkedIn translated | Twitter condensed | WeChat article |
| Twitter thread | Publish | LinkedIn expanded | XHS translated | Blog post |
| Blog article | Publish | LinkedIn excerpt | Twitter thread | XHS summary |

### Cross-Platform Hooks
- LinkedIn: "I wrote about this on my blog (link in comments)..."
- Twitter: "Expanded thread from my LinkedIn post..."
- XHS: "åœ¨LinkedInä¸Šåˆ†äº«äº†è¿™ä¸ªè§‚ç‚¹ï¼Œä¸­æ–‡ç‰ˆåœ¨è¿™é‡Œ..."
