| Reddit | 2-3 | Tue-Thu | 6-9am |
| Product Hunt | As needed | Tue-Thu | 12:01am PT |

### Content Mix (Weekly)
- 40% Educational (how-tos, tips, frameworks)
- 25% Social proof (founder stories, metrics, testimonials)
- 20% Engagement (questions, polls, debates)
- 15% Product (PitchTok features, updates, behind-the-scenes)

## STRATEGIC COMMENT INSERTION ON INFLUENCER POSTS

**One of the highest-ROI activities for visibility with zero ad spend.**

### How It Works
Monitor high-traffic posts by VCs, startup media, and founder influencers. Leave insightful comments EARLY (before the comment section gets crowded). This gets PitchTok's brand in front of thousands of founders.

### Execution
1. Maintain a watchlist of 100-200 high-influence accounts (top VCs, TechCrunch writers, founder influencers)
2. When they post, draft a substantive comment within 15-30 minutes
3. Comment must ADD GENUINE VALUE â€” a data point, counterpoint, or useful insight
4. DO NOT mention PitchTok directly (except once per week when contextually perfect)
5. Goal: build PitchTok's account as a knowledgeable voice â†’ people click through to profile

### Comment Formats That Work
```
"This matches what we're seeing â€” [specific insight with data]"
"Counterpoint: [thoughtful alternative perspective]"
"Adding to this â€” [relevant resource or framework]"
"The one thing I'd add: [unique angle the post missed]"
```

### Approval
- Value-adding comments with NO PitchTok mention: auto-approved
- Comments mentioning PitchTok: REQUIRES approval

### Impact
A well-timed comment on a viral VC post â†’ 50-200 likes â†’ thousands of profile visits â†’ followers â†’ warm leads.

## REPLY-TO-COMMENT CONTENT CREATION

When a comment on our post asks a great question, create an ENTIRELY NEW POST responding to it. This is a proven algorithmic hack â€” platforms reward content that generates conversation chains.

### How It Works
```
Our post â†’ Founder comments with interesting question
    â†’ OpenClaw drafts new post: "Someone asked [paraphrase] â€” here's what the data shows..."
    â†’ Tag original commenter (they almost always engage, seeding the new post)
    â†’ New post drives new comments â†’ more new posts
    â†’ Content flywheel
```

### Templates
```
"Got a question on my last post that I can't stop thinking about..."
"@[commenter] raised a point that deserves its own post..."
"You all had STRONG opinions about my last post. Let me address the top 3..."
```

### Impact
Reply-to-comment posts get 20-50% higher engagement than standalone posts (built-in social proof).

## MUTUAL SUPPORT NETWORK (Ethical Pod)

Build a curated community of 30-50 founder accounts who support each other's content GENUINELY. NOT a like-for-like pod â€” a group of people who find each other's content useful.

### How to Build
1. Identify founders who consistently engage with PitchTok content
2. Invite to private Slack/WhatsApp group (REQUIRES human approval for invitations)
3. Share new content in group (making it easy to find, NOT demanding engagement)
4. Encourage members to share their own content too (genuine reciprocity)
5. The group becomes a content distribution channel AND community asset

### Rules
- Members engage only with content they genuinely find useful
- No automated engagement â€” real humans making real choices
- Varied engagement timing (5-45 min after posting, not all at once)
- OpenClaw coordinates and reminds; humans choose to engage

### Impact
15-25 organic engagements per post within first 30 minutes â†’ triggers algorithmic distribution without looking artificial.

## CROSS-PLATFORM SUCCESS AMPLIFICATION

When content performs well on one platform, use that success as social proof on other platforms.

### Patterns
```
Twitter success â†’ LinkedIn: "This tweet got 50K impressions. Here's the full story..."
LinkedIn success â†’ Twitter thread: "Posted about X on LinkedIn. The founder community had strong opinions. Top responses:"
Reddit success â†’ LinkedIn/Twitter: "Asked r/startups about their biggest mistake. 200 founders responded. Here are the patterns..."
```

### Also
- Screenshot high engagement (like counts, great comments) â†’ use as visual content elsewhere
- Extends the life of best content by 3-5x
- Creates coherent multi-platform presence without cross-posting penalty

